<topic template="Default" status="Under Construction" lasteditedby="Adam" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../../../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Indexer</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">An </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Indexer</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> is a cam device that is pre-assembled with an input and output shaft. When the input-shaft (cam) rotates continuously, the output-shaft &#160; moves, in steps, in one direction. The </text><text styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">&apos;index&apos;</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> motion is also called a </text><text styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">&apos;progressive&apos;</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> motion.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">The output-shaft rotates progressively, in one direction, with a series of identical motions. After a number of index motions, the output-shaft rotates returns to its original position. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#ff6600;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName-small"><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Some definitions used with Indexers</text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">:</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box2" translate="true">NUMBER-OF-STOPS</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">: The number of times the input shaft must rotate to index the output shaft one complete cycle. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box2" translate="true">INDEX PERIOD</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">: The rotation, in degrees, of the input shaft to complete the </text><text styleclass="Popup Box2" translate="true">INDEX</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box2" translate="true">DWELL PERIOD</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">: The rotation, in degrees, of the input shaft to complete the DWELL. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box2"><text styleclass="Popup Box2" translate="true">INDEX PERIOD + DWELL PERIOD</text><text styleclass="Popup Box2" translate="true"> = 360. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box2" translate="true">TYPE: 1, 2, 3</text><text styleclass="Popup Box2" translate="true">:</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> number of </text><text styleclass="Popup Box2" translate="true">INDEX-PERIODS</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> as the Input Shaft rotates once.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
</topic>
